        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Construction of Water Storage Tanks for Drip Irrigation&amp;quot; introduced by the Agriculture, Farmers Welfare and Cooperation Department, Gujarat,  aims to offer financial assistance to farmers for setting up cemented water tanks essential for efficient drip irrigation.  It supports sustainable agriculture through water conservation, especially for horticultural practices.\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n  - **Unit cost of construction:** ₹1,00,000/- per tank.  - **For General category farmers:** 50% subsidy, up to ₹50,000/-.  - **For SC/ST farmers:** 75% subsidy, up to ₹75,000/-.\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme provides financial assistance to farmers across Gujarat for constructing water storage tanks to support drip irrigation, with cost-sharing benefits based on farmer category.",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
